Subject: [PATCH 7/8] PCI: Remove DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE macro use
Patch-mainline: v3.17-rc1
Git-commit: 9baa3c34ac4e27f7e062f266f50cc5dbea26a6c1 (partial)
References: bsc#922842 Fate#318524

We should prefer `struct pci_device_id` over `DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE` to
meet kernel coding style guidelines.  This issue was reported by checkpatch.

A simplified version of the semantic patch that makes this change is as
follows (http://coccinelle.lip6.fr/):

// <smpl>

@@
identifier i;
declarer name DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE;
initializer z;
@@

- DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE(i)
+ const struct pci_device_id i[]
= z;

// </smpl>

[bhelgaas: add semantic patch]
Signed-off-by: Benoit Taine <benoit.taine@lip6.fr>
Signed-off-by: Bjorn Helgaas <bhelgaas@google.com>
Acked-by: Cho, Yu-Chen <acho@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igbvf/netdev.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igbvf/netdev.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igbvf/netdev.c
@@ -2853,7 +2853,7 @@ static const struct pci_error_handlers i
 	.resume = igbvf_io_resume,
 };
 
-static DEFINE_PCI_DEVICE_TABLE(igbvf_pci_tbl) = {
+static const struct pci_device_id igbvf_pci_tbl[] = {
 	{ PCI_VDEVICE(INTEL, E1000_DEV_ID_82576_VF), board_vf },
 	{ PCI_VDEVICE(INTEL, E1000_DEV_ID_I350_VF), board_i350_vf },
